This paper deals with the performance analysis of device-to-device communication in LTE networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the impact of different configuration settings on system performance, which is related to information theory and signal processing, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also proposes a modified HARQ process to mitigate scalability constraints, which is related to control systems and robotics, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category. The paper also deals with reliability and security, which are related to cryptography and security, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the control of autonomous vehicles, which is related to multimedia and computer vision, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category.
